{
  "text": "Bird. I am guessing it might be a messenger. The two pads depicted by the position of the wings, bringing catalyst, which could be used to polarize on either path. Is this in any way correct? Aye. And well, it is a correct perception that the position of the winged creature is significant the a more correct perception of this entity and its significance is the realization that the mind, a body, a spirit complex is having made contact with its potentiated self, now beginning its flight towards that a great logos, which is that which is sought by the adept. Further, the nature of the winged creature is echoed both by the female holding it and the symbol of the female upon which the figures, a feet, rest. That is the nature of a catalyst is overwhelmingly of an unconsciousness coming from that which is not of the mind and which has no connection with the intellect, as you call it, which precedes or is concomitant with catholytic action, all uses of catalyst by the mind are those consciously applied to catalyst without conscious intent.",
